edu.ucla.sspace.util

Class CharMap<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<Character,V>
      • edu.ucla.sspace.util.CharMap<V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Map<Character,V>

    public class CharMap<V>
extends AbstractMap<Character,V>
implements Serializable
    A space-optimized map for associating char keys with values.

    This class makes a trade off for reduced space usage at the cost of decreased performace. The put, get, containsKey and get operations are all logarithmic when the map is unmodified. If a new mapping is added, or one is removed, the operation is linear in the number of mappings. Both size and isEmpty are still constant time.

    The get operation runs in logarithmic time. The set operation runs in consant time if setting an existing non-zero value to a non-zero value. However, if the set invocation sets a zero value to non-zero, the operation is linear with the size of the array.

    This map allows null values.

    Iteration ordering follows the natural ordering of char values, with the lowest char key value being returned first. Implementation Note: the Iterator.remove() method is currently unsupported and will throw an exception when called. However, a future implementation will fix this.

    Author:
    David Jurgens
    See Also:
    TrieMap, IntegerMap, Map, Serialized Form
